500			! number of atoms
1.0			! temperature (~40K but it is a greater effective temperature)
250			! system box length 
0.45		! bond length (LJ reduced units)
109.5		! bond angle (degrees)    
1.0			! sigma: effective non-bonded atomic size (LJ reduced units)
1.0			! epsilon: LJ potential well depth (LJ reduced units)
1.0			! mass: mass of the C's (LJ reduced units) 
1			! shift: 1 or 0 to apply or not a shift to the LJ potential
2.5			! rc: cutoff radius of non-bonded interactions
5.0			! maxDih: maximum dihedral angle variation (degrees)
10000		! N_MCEQUI: number of Monte Carlo step in equilibration
10000	! N_MCPROD: number of Monte Carlo steps in production
497			! NATTEMPTS: number of attempts to change a dihedral angle per MC step
20		! NSAVE: for every NSAVE steps, 1 data point is stored
! EOF (This line is necessary for the compilation in old compilers, aka the one available in cerqt)